Why This Exists
---------------

I spend most of my time writing C++ — routing engines, embedded firmware, public SDKs.
Web development is not my day job, and this site was never meant to be a portfolio piece
for frontend work.

I built it because I wanted a resume that felt like me: dark, technical, a little
over-engineered for what it is. The floating C++ snippets in the background, the
typewriter that cycles through what I'm actually shipping, the glass cards — none of
that was strictly necessary. I did it anyway, because I care about the craft even when
it's outside my lane.

The structure is open for anyone to read. If you are a C++ engineer who wants a resume
site and finds this useful as a reference, that is exactly the kind of person I built it
for. Take the ideas. Don't copy the content — the words, the CV, the photo, and the
professional history belong to me.


